<h3>Real-World Focus</h3>
<p>Through case studies, role-plays, and simulations based on real business situations, you''ll practice the skills you need in authentic contexts. Topics include marketing, finance, human resources, international trade, and more.</p>

<h3>Course Fees</h3>
<p>Minimum 4 weeks<br/>
Weekly fee: NZ$390</p>',
390.00, 'NZD', '/static/images/course-business-english.jpg', 0, 1, 'online', 5, datetime('now'), datetime('now'));

-- Course 6: Academic English & University Pathway
INSERT INTO product (id, name, slug, summary, description_html, price, price_unit, featured_image, is_recommended, is_active, status, `order`, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
(6, 'Academic English & University Pathway', 'academic-english-pathway',
'Prepare for university study in New Zealand with academic skills training. Covers essay writing, research skills, note-taking, critical thinking, and academic presentation. Partner university pathways available. Ideal for students planning tertiary education.',
'<h2>Course Overview</h2>
<p>The Academic English & University Pathway course prepares international students for success in New Zealand universities and other English-medium tertiary institutions. Develop the academic language skills and study techniques needed to excel in higher education.</p>

<h3>Academic Skills Covered</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Academic Writing:</strong> Essays, research papers, referencing (APA, Harvard), academic style and tone</li>
  <li><strong>Research Skills:</strong> Finding and evaluating sources, academic integrity, avoiding plagiarism</li>
  <li><strong>Reading:</strong> Efficient reading strategies for academic texts, critical reading, analyzing arguments</li>
  <li><strong>Listening:</strong> Note-taking from lectures, understanding academic discourse</li>
  <li><strong>Speaking & Presentations:</strong> Seminar participation, academic presentations, group discussions</li>
  <li><strong>Critical Thinking:</strong> Analyzing, evaluating, and synthesizing information</li>
</ul>

<h3>University Pathway Option</h3>
<p>Successfully completing this course at the required level may provide direct entry to partner universities without IELTS or PTE tests. Please enquire about current pathway agreements.</p>

<h3>Course Structure</h3>
<p>Monday to Friday, 9:00 AM - 3:30 PM<br/>
26 hours per week<br/>
12-24 week duration recommended<br/>
Entry requirement: Intermediate to Upper-Intermediate level English</p>

<h3>Course Fees</h3>
<p>Minimum 12 weeks<br/>
Weekly fee: NZ$400</p>',
400.00, 'NZD', '/static/images/course-academic-english-pathway.jpg', 0, 1, 'online', 6, datetime('now'), datetime('now'));

-- Course 7: English Plus Activities
INSERT INTO product (id, name, slug, summary, description_html, price, price_unit, featured_image, is_recommended, is_active, status, `order`, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
(7, 'English Plus Activities', 'english-plus-activities',
'Combine English learning with exciting New Zealand activities. Morning English classes plus organized afternoon activities including surfing, kayaking, hiking, cultural tours, and adventure sports. Perfect for active learners wanting to experience New Zealand culture.',
'<h2>Course Overview</h2>
<p>The English Plus Activities program combines quality English language learning with exciting activities that showcase the best of New Zealand. Perfect for students who want to improve their English while experiencing Kiwi culture and the stunning natural environment.</p>

<h3>How It Works</h3>
<p><strong>Mornings:</strong> General English classes (15 hours per week)<br/>
<strong>Afternoons:</strong> Organized activities and excursions (3 afternoons per week)</p>

<h3>Sample Activities</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Water Sports:</strong> Surfing lessons at Browns Bay Beach, kayaking, paddle boarding, sailing</li>
  <li><strong>Adventure:</strong> Bush walks, coastal hiking, rock climbing, high ropes course</li>
  <li><strong>Cultural Experiences:</strong> Maori cultural tours, museum visits, Auckland city tours</li>
  <li><strong>Social Activities:</strong> Beach BBQs, sports games, movie nights, café culture</li>
  <li><strong>Weekend Trips:</strong> Optional paid excursions to Bay of Islands, Rotorua, Hobbiton, Waiheke Island</li>
</ul>

<h3>What''s Included</h3>
<ul>
  <li>15 hours of English classes per week</li>
  <li>3 organized activities per week</li>
  <li>Activity equipment and instruction</li>
  <li>Transport to activity locations</li>
  <li>Experienced activity leaders</li>
  <li>Course materials</li>
  <li>Travel insurance assistance</li>
</ul>

<h3>Perfect For</h3>
<p>Gap year students, young learners (16-25), active travelers, anyone wanting to combine language learning with adventure and cultural immersion.</p>

<h3>Course Structure</h3>
<p>2-8 week programs available<br/>
Age requirement: 16-30 years<br/>
All English levels welcome</p>

<h3>Course Fees</h3>
<p>Weekly fee: NZ$450 (includes classes and activities)<br/>
Accommodation packages available</p>

<p><strong>Limited availability</strong> - book in advance for summer months (December-February)</p>',
450.00, 'NZD', '/static/images/course-english-plus-activities.jpg', 0, 1, 'online', 7, datetime('now'), datetime('now'));

-- Course 8: One-to-One Private Tuition
INSERT INTO product (id, name, slug, summary, description_html, price, price_unit, featured_image, is_recommended, is_active, status, `order`, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
(8, 'One-to-One Private Tuition', 'private-tuition',
'Personalized English lessons tailored to your specific needs and goals. Flexible scheduling, customized curriculum, and focused attention from experienced teachers. Ideal for executives, professionals with specific requirements, or students needing targeted support.',
'<h2>Course Overview</h2>
<p>One-to-One Private Tuition offers the ultimate in personalized English language learning. With complete flexibility and lessons designed specifically for your needs, this is the fastest and most effective way to achieve your English language goals.</p>

<h3>Why Choose Private Tuition?</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>100% Focused Attention:</strong> Your teacher''s complete attention for maximum learning efficiency</li>
  <li><strong>Customized Curriculum:</strong> Lessons designed around your specific goals, interests, and professional needs</li>
  <li><strong>Flexible Scheduling:</strong> Choose times that suit your schedule, including evenings and weekends</li>
  <li><strong>Rapid Progress:</strong> Intensive, focused learning accelerates improvement</li>
  <li><strong>Specific Focus Areas:</strong> Target exactly what you need - pronunciation, presentations, writing, exam prep, etc.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Popular Private Tuition Goals</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Executive English for senior professionals</li>
  <li>English for specific industries (medical, legal, IT, engineering, etc.)</li>
  <li>Intensive exam preparation (PTE, IELTS, Cambridge)</li>
  <li>Presentation and public speaking skills</li>
  <li>Academic writing for thesis or research papers</li>
  <li>Pronunciation and accent coaching</li>
  <li>Job interview preparation</li>
  <li>Fast-track general English improvement</li>
</ul>

<h3>How It Works</h3>
<p>1. <strong>Needs Analysis:</strong> We discuss your goals, level, and specific requirements<br/>
2. <strong>Customized Plan:</strong> Your teacher designs a personalized learning plan<br/>
3. <strong>Flexible Schedule:</strong> Book lessons at times that suit you<br/>
4. <strong>Progress Tracking:</strong> Regular assessment and adjustment of your program</p>

<h3>Lesson Options</h3>
<p>Minimum booking: 5 hours<br/>
Available: Monday-Saturday, 8:00 AM - 7:00 PM<br/>
Location: Browns Bay Language School or online via Zoom</p>

<h3>Fees</h3>
<p>Hourly rate: NZ$95 per hour<br/>
Discounted packages available for 20+ hours</p>

<p><strong>Contact us</strong> to discuss your requirements and schedule a needs analysis meeting.</p>',
95.00, 'NZD', '/static/images/course-private-tuition.jpg', 0, 1, 'online', 8, datetime('now'), datetime('now'));

